.TH JTUTIL-SEED "1" "June 2026" "jtutil manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-seed \- Run jtcore repeatedly with different seeds
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs jtcore repeatedly with different \fB\-\-seed\fR values until one build passes or \fB\-\-max\-trials\fR is reached.
.SS "Options consumed by jtutil seed must appear before core:"
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-trials\fR n
Stop after n seed builds
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR n
Run up to n jtcore seed builds at the same time
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR=\fI\,n\/\fR
Same as \fB\-\-parallel\fR n
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR | \fB\-h\fR
Show this summary
.PP
The remaining arguments are passed to jtcore. Each jtcore run gets a distinct
\fB\-\-seed\fR and \fB\-\-output\fR folder. The Quartus build runs under <output>/build,
and its console output is written to <output>/jtcore.log. Runs invoke jtcore
with \fB\-\-nocopy\fR and \fB\-u\fR JTFRAME_NOSTA; as jobs finish, jtutil seed copies
the best RBF seen so far into the normal release/<target>/ folder. The default
output base is:
.IP
$JTROOT/cores/<core\-name>/seed/<target>
.PP
Create a jtseed.last file in the current folder to stop after the current batch.
.PP
Use "man jtutil\-seed" for full documentation.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil seed [flags] <core> [jtcore options]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for seed
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-trials\fR int
Stop after n seed builds (default 100)
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR int
Run up to n jtcore seed builds at the same time (default 1)
.TP
\fB\-\-stop\fR
Stop when a build is STA clean (default true)
.TP
\fB\-\-zero\fR
Start with seed zero (default true)
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
